parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil cooler can cause oil to leak into the exhaust manifold, leading to heavy smoke, potential fires, and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, the oil leak can cause damage to other engine components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: heavy smoke coming from underneath the car
sagging or leaning of the front and rear ends of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose visibility of critical vehicle information, such as speed, fuel level, and warning indicators, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.

the turn signal visual and audible indicators fail
making it impossible to know if/when the turn signal is activated.
